	<pb facs="liv_020026_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="inspace" rend="gray sup" hand="#U">57</add> <space extent="4" unit="words"/><date when="1845-10-08">October 8th 1845</date></p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Honoured Fathers, and respected friends
<lb/>of the <orgName><settlement>London</settlement> Missionary Society</orgName></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="3" unit="words"/>I have always been deeply
<lb/>concerned about the education of my children,
<lb/>but never more so than at the present time
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>I always had a wish to send my children out
<lb/>of <region>Cafferland</region> to some good school; but <del >not</del><add place="over-text">was</add> not
<lb/>able to do it both for want of a place to send
<lb/>them as well as that my pecuniary circumstances
<lb/>did not admit of it.</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="3" unit="words"/>You will have heard with much
<lb/><choice><sic>greif</sic><corr>grief</corr></choice> that two of my sons have adopted the
<lb/>customs of our heathen ancestory which while
<lb/>it deeply <choice><sic>greives</sic><corr>grieves</corr></choice> me has done great injury to
<lb/>the cause of God.</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>This event made me doubly
<lb/>anxious to send my younger children to school
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>I have therefore sent three of my daughters 
<lb/>to a school established at the <orgName><term type="collective">English</term> Residency</orgName>


	<pb facs="liv_020026_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>in <geogName>Tyumie Vale</geogName> <region>Cafferland</region> by the Lady of the
<lb/><choice><sic>welknown</sic><corr>well known</corr></choice> Diplomatic Agent and <choice><sic>freind</sic><corr>friend</corr></choice> of the
<lb/><term type="collective">Native</term> tribes of this country and kept by an
<lb/><choice><sic>exelent</sic><corr>excellent</corr></choice> young lady from the Church of our
<lb/>friend <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Jack</persName> of <settlement>Bristol</settlement></p> 
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>At this school are at present 21
<lb/>children who are fed and clothed, with one
<lb/>exception gratuitously, <persName>Miss Harding</persName> has
<lb/>hitherto <choice><sic>cheifly</sic><corr>chiefly</corr></choice> depended for support to herself
<lb/>and pupils on <persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi> Stretch</persName> and a few <choice><sic>freinds</sic><corr>friends</corr></choice></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="words"/>From my place I have sent 8 children
<lb/>now while I hope that I shall try to do what I can
<lb/>for my children, I feel that I shall not be able
<lb/>to do what I ought, My object in writing is kindly
<lb/>to request the Directors to assist me, to meet
<lb/>the <choice><sic>expence</sic><corr>expense</corr></choice> connected with their education
<lb/>whilest it will be gratifying to my feelings as
<lb/>a <term type="collective">Christian</term> parent, it will <unclear><choice><sic>redound</sic><corr>rebound</corr></choice></unclear> to the good
<lb/>of <choice><sic>Gods</sic><corr>God's</corr></choice> cause generally, as the <orgName>Tyumie Seminary</orgName> <!-- coded Tyumie as geogName earlier but now not sure if it's settlement too/instead? HB -->
<lb/>for the instruction of young females is one of the
<lb/>best establishments of the kind in <region>Cafferland</region>.</p> <!-- Same q's as above for Cafferland. HB -->
<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="words"/>Will you allow me <choice><sic>Reverand</sic><corr>Reverend</corr></choice> Gentleman
<lb/>to recommend it to you, and the churches generally
<lb/>in <country>England</country></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="5" unit="words"/>I remain
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/>Yours very sincerely
<lb/><space extent="7" unit="words"/><persName>Jan Tzatzoe</persName></p>

